cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV

The paper focuses on the design, optimization, and flight control of Flapping Wing Micro Air Vehicles (FWMAVs) using simulation and reinforcement learning. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of reinforcement learning and deep learning for control also suggests the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the simulation involves modeling and analyzing the flight dynamics of FWMAVs, which could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing visual data from the simulation.
